SUBENT        F0795004   20251225   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  5         13
REACTION   (9-F-19(P,G)10-NE-20,PAR,DA,,REL)
            No information about units.
SAMPLE     The target was held at 45 degr. to the beam in a
           cylindrical brass chamber with 6 mm thick walls.
DETECTOR   (NAICR) NaI crystal could be rotated about the vertical
           axis through the target spot so that the front surface
           of the crystal was displaced 4.5 cm from the target
           and target chamber axis. A 2.5*4.4 NaI(TI) crystal in
           a fixed position served as a monitor. The angular
           rotation of the NaI crystal was limited in the range
           from -150 degr. to +150 degr.
STATUS     (CURVE,,K.M.Subotic+,J,NP/A,331,491,1979) Fig.4
HISTORY    (20251225U) SD: STATUS updated.
ENDBIB              13
